title: Elation and relief for some families as first Israeli hostages are freed
description: The Israeli women and children released Friday, ranging in age from 5 to 85, were among an estimated 240 taken on Oct. 7 to Gaza by Hamas and other militants.

title: 12 Thai hostages freed from Gaza, Thai prime minister says
description: The Thai nationals were released Friday during a pause in fighting between Hamas and Israel; 13 Israeli hostages also were released.

title: 34 pro-Palestinian protesters arrested for disrupting Macy’s parade, police say
description: Some of the pro-Palestinian protesters arrested in New York on Thanksgiving had jumped the barricades and glued themselves to Sixth Avenue, according to police.

title: Who was to blame for Diana’s death? ‘The Crown’ vs. the historical record.
description: The Netflix series emphasizes the paparazzi while only vaguely nodding to the role of the driver. Here’s what French and British investigators determined.

title: Guns over Gaza fall silent, Israel-Hamas hostage release deal moves forward
description: The uneasy calm will last for four days, giving a chance for aid to enter the Gaza Strip as a carefully choreographed exchange takes place of hostages held by Hamas for Palestinians in Israeli jails.

title: Olympian Oscar Pistorius will be released from prison on parole
description: Oscar Pistorius, the South African Olympic sprinter who killed his girlfriend, Reeva Steenkamp, will be released on Jan. 5.

title: Far-right protesters burn and loot Dublin in worst violence ‘in decades’
description: A stabbing rumored to involve someone with an immigrant background turned into a rallying cry for right-wing protesters who went on to ravage downtown Dublin.

title: The Taiwan party toughest on China has a strong lead as election nears
description: The China-skeptical Democratic Progressive Party is leading in the polls ahead of January’s presidential election, igniting fears about Chinese military aggression.

title: Russian and Chinese executives discuss Russia-Crimea tunnel project
description: Talks about building a tunnel between Russia and Crimea were triggered by Russian concerns over the security of an 11-mile bridge across the Kerch Strait.

title: New Zealand shifts to the right, but only slightly by global standards
description: The center-right National Party will form a government with two smaller parties. Political veteran and China hawk Winston Peters will become foreign minister.

title: In the jungle with Myanmar’s oldest rebel group amid new threat to junta
description: While much attention has focused on insurgents led by exiled pro-democracy figures, it is increasingly ethnic rebel groups like the KNU that are defining the conflict.

title: Israel-Gaza war live updates: Highly anticipated pause in fighting, hostage release expected in coming hours
description: A four-day pause in fighting is expected to begin at 7 a.m, followed by a release of hostages at 4 p.m., according to Qatar, which is acting as mediator.
